[[File:Tree_Of_Life_(with_horizontal_gene_transfer).svg|thumb]]
[[File:Elysia_chlorotica_by_Gould_1.jpg|thumb]]（Elysia chlorotica）擁有[[盜食體質|盜食體質]]，可吸收[[藻類|藻類]]中的[[葉綠體|葉綠體]]。使用[[葉綠體|葉綠體]]基因的[[光合作用|光合作用]]繼續可達12個月，這是因為藻類核基因被轉移到定向海蛞蝓細胞核內。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Transcriptomic Evidence for the Expression of Horizontally Transferred Algal Nuclear Genes in the Photosynthetic Sea Slug, Elysia chlorotica|journal=Molecular Biology and Evolution|url=https://academic.oup.com/mbe/article/29/6/1545/996402|date=2012-06-01|volume=29|issue=6|doi=10.1093/molbev/msr316|pages=1545–1556|issn=0737-4038|language=en|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=Sidney K. Pierce, Xiaodong Fang, Julie A. Schwartz, Xuanting Jiang, Wei Zhao, Nicholas E. Curtis, Kevin M. Kocot, Bicheng Yang, Jian Wang|archive-date=2018-06-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180601223942/https://academic.oup.com/mbe/article/29/6/1545/996402|dead-url=no}}</ref>]]

'''基因水平轉移'''（{{lang-en|horizontal gene transfer}}，[[縮寫|縮寫]]：{{lang|en|HGT}}）又稱'''水平基因轉殖'''或'''基因側向轉移'''（{{lang|en|lateral gene transfer}}，[[縮寫|縮寫]]：{{lang|en|LGT}}），指生物將遺傳物質傳遞給其他細胞而非其子代的過程，例如：[[接合|接合]]、[[转导|转导]]及[[轉化_(生物)|转化]]。與此相對，“基因垂直传递”指生物由其祖先繼承遺傳物質。[[遺傳學|遺傳學]]一般關心更爲普遍的垂直傳遞，但目前的知識表明，基因水平轉移是一個重要的現象<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20527441.500-horizontal-and-vertical-the-evolution-of-evolution.html?full=true&print=true |title=Horizontal and vertical: The evolution of evolution - life - 26 January 2010 - New Scientist |accessdate=2010-01-29 |archive-date=2015-04-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150402135537/http://www.newscientist.com/article/mg20527441.500-horizontal-and-vertical-the-evolution-of-evolution.html?full=true&print=true |dead-url=no }}</ref>。由於此現象的存在，使生物早期的演化關係更為複雜。

水平基因轉移是細菌[[抗生素抗藥性|抗生素抗藥性]]的主要原因<ref>OECD, ''Safety Assessment of Transgenic Organisms, Volume 4: OECD Consensus Documents,'' 2010, pp.171-174</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Kay E, Vogel TM, Bertolla F, Nalin R, Simonet P |title=In situ transfer of antibiotic resistance genes from transgenic (transplastomic) tobacco plants to bacteria |journal=Appl. Environ. Microbiol. |volume=68 |issue=7 |pages=3345–51 |date=July 2002 |pmid=12089013 |pmc=126776 |url=http://aem.asm.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=12089013 |access-date=2014-02-09 |archive-date=2020-06-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200605112611/https://aem.asm.org/content/68/7/3345.long |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Koonin EV, Makarova KS, Aravind L |title=Horizontal gene transfer in prokaryotes: quantification and classification |journal=Annu. Rev. Microbiol. |volume=55 |pages=709–742 |year=2001 |pmid=11544372 |doi=10.1146/annurev.micro.55.1.709 |url=http://arjournals.annualreviews.org/doi/full/10.1146/annurev.micro.55.1.709?url_ver=Z39.88-2003&rfr_id=ori:rid:crossref.org&rfr_dat=cr_pub%3dpubmed |access-date=2014-02-09 |archive-date=2019-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919003156/https://www.annualreviews.org/doi/full/10.1146/annurev.micro.55.1.709?url_ver=Z39.88-2003&rfr_id=ori:rid:crossref.org&rfr_dat=cr_pub=pubmed |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |author=Nielsen KM |title=Barriers to horizontal gene transfer by natural transformation in soil bacteria |journal=APMIS Suppl. |volume=84 |pages=77–84 |year=1998 |pmid=9850687 }}</ref>，並且在細菌可降解新型化合物例如人類創建的殺蟲劑進化中起著重要作用<ref>{{cite journal |author=McGowan C, Fulthorpe R, Wright A, Tiedje JM |title=Evidence for interspecies gene transfer in the evolution of 2,4-dichlorophenoxyacetic acid degraders |journal=Appl. Environ. Microbiol. |volume=64 |issue=10 |pages=4089–92 |date=October 1998 |pmid=9758850 |pmc=106609 |url=http://aem.asm.org/cgi/pmidlookup?view=long&pmid=9758850 |access-date=2014-02-09 |archive-date=2019-09-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190919003255/https://aem.asm.org/content/64/10/4089.long |dead-url=no }}</ref>，並在進化，維護和傳輸毒性的重要原因 <ref name="doi10.3389/fcimb.2012.00161">{{cite journal|title=Paradigms of pathogenesis: targeting the mobile genetic elements of disease|date=2012|journal=Frontiers in Cellular and Infection Microbiology|volume=2|doi=10.3389/fcimb.2012.00161|language=en|issn=2235-2988|url=http://journal.frontiersin.org/article/10.3389/fcimb.2012.00161/abstract|accessdate=2018-04-02|author=Eric Christopher Keen}}</ref>。這種基因水平轉移經常涉及溫和的[[噬菌體|噬菌體]]和[[質粒|質粒]]<ref>{{Cite journal |author=Naik GA, Bhat LN, Chpoade BA, Lynch JM |title=Transfer of broad-host-range antibiotic resistance plasmids in soil microcosms |url=https://archive.org/details/sim_current-microbiology_1994-04_28_4/page/209 |journal=Curr. Microbiol. |volume=28 |year=1994 |pages=209–215 |doi = 10.1007/BF01575963 |issue=4}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal |author=Varga M, Kuntova L, Pantucek R, Maslanova I, Ruzickova V, Doskar J |title = Efficient transfer of antibiotic resistance plasmids by transduction within methicillin-resistant ''Staphylococcus aureus'' USA300 clone |journal=FEMS Microbiol. Lett. |volume=332 |year=2012 |pages=146–152 |doi = 10.1111/j.1574-6968.2012.02589.x |issue=2 |pmid=22553940}}</ref>。

大多數的思維在遺傳學一直專注於垂直傳遞，但是人們日益認識到基因水平轉移是一種非常顯著的現象，以及是在單細胞生物之間或許是基因轉移主要形式<ref name="edwards">{{cite web |url = http://www.physorg.com/news205389256.html |title = Horizontal gene transfer in microbes much more frequent than previously thought |author = Lin Edwards |date = October 4, 2010 |publisher = PhysOrg.com |accessdate = 2012-01-06 |archive-date = 2011-09-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110915023151/http://www.physorg.com/news205389256.html |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref name="arnold">{{cite web |url = http://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=to-share-and-share-alike |title = To Share and Share Alike: Bacteria swap genes with their neighbors more frequently than researchers have realized |author = Carrie Arnold |date = April 18, 2011 |publisher = Scientific American |accessdate = 2012-01-06 |archive-date = 2012-11-02 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20121102062024/https://www.scientificamerican.com/article.cfm?id=to-share-and-share-alike |dead-url = no }}</ref>。

人工的基因水平轉移屬於[[基因工程|基因工程]]的一種。

